Read File into R from OSF without Losing your Mind

Jamie Reilly PhD

May 2025

THE PROBLEM

You want to read a data file (e.g., .rda, .csv, .xlsx) into R by downloading it directly from a public repository on the project page of the OSF. Things get weird really damn quickly. Heres what to do.

THE SOLUTION

Step 1

Start on the OSF project page for your project of interest. Click on the files tab.

Step 2

Click on the file of interest. Ill point to one.

Step 3.

Copy the URL in your browser bar. Thats almost your download link.

Step 4

Add /download to the path. This is the part they dont want you to know about.

LIVE ACTION

You can read the file in two steps it all depends on its format (e.g., csv, rda).

# Remember to enclose your path in quotes single or double doesn't matter just
# don't mix
my_url <- "https://osf.io/mwg8q/download"
my_dat <- read.csv(my_url)
print(my_dat)
